title: M20 Got my first job AMA
author: coolman3475
text:
Got my first internship yesterday, however I am confident it will convert into a full time job.
I am currently a CS freshman but picked up coding at home with python, and used pygame for simple game development, especially to learn OOD. I practiced a bit of HTML, CSS and JS aswell before the job interview. However, the only real project that got me hired was a space invaders like game written in Python on under 500 lines of code. I was surprised that it impressed them, however, I believe I was very confident in the interview really played up that project, especially enfissising the OOD and inheritance.  You can check out ghat project and various others om my github.

Anyways if any of you would like to pick my brain and AMA go ahead.

Although I am only an intermediate programmer. I have progressed extremely quickly thus far. The main 2 factors which have contributed my learning and thinking process have been systems theory (way of conceptualizing) and utilizing language modeled (chatGPT). I will make extensive documentation on my methods of approaching these topics on the future. So stay tuned and AMA. alsoheck out my github if you like..
